OL,3,CSolicitor jailed after stealing
OL,4,C#84,000 from elderly clients
OL,6,FThe offence was reported to police
OL,7,Fafter a care provider contacted the
OL,8,Fvictim's family informing them they'd
OL,9,Fbeen unable to take payment for care
OL,10,Fdue to insufficient funds in his
OL,11,Faccount.
OL,13,FGriffiths was arrested and admitted to
OL,14,Fthe offences during interview.
OL,16,FDC Dominic Maidment said: "These are
OL,17,Ftwo awful situations where Griffiths
OL,18,Fhas taken advantage of her position
OL,19,Fand stolen tens of thousands of pounds
OL,20,Ffrom two vulnerable adults, one of
OL,21,Fwhom is sadly no longer with us.
