OL,6,F"As power of attorney, Griffiths was
OL,7,Fexpected to safeguard the finances of
OL,8,Fthe victims and act on their behalf in
OL,9,Ftheir best interests.
OL,11,F"Instead, she has abused their trust
OL,12,Fby transferring significant sums of
OL,13,Fmoney from their accounts into hers,
OL,14,Fmeaning that in one of the cases,
OL,15,Fthere was no money to pay for the
OL,16,Fvictim's care."
